-- TALKING_STAGE - Reflection blocks (7)
('reflection', 'It sounds like you''re in the talking stage and things feel unclear about where this is heading, and that ambiguity is really hard to sit with.', ARRAY['talking_stage', 'unclear', 'ambiguity'], ARRAY['confused', 'frustrated'], 1, 50, true),
('reflection', 'Being in the talking stage can make you feel like you''re in limbo, not knowing if this will turn into something more or if it''s just casual, and that uncertainty is exhausting.', ARRAY['talking_stage', 'limbo', 'uncertainty'], ARRAY['confused', 'tired'], 2, 50, true),
('reflection', 'It sounds like part of you wants to know where things stand, but another part might be afraid of what that clarity might mean, and that conflict is really difficult.', ARRAY['talking_stage', 'clarity', 'fear'], ARRAY['confused', 'worried'], 2, 50, true),
('reflection', 'The talking stage often makes you question whether you''re allowed to want more or ask for clarity, and that uncertainty about your own needs is really challenging.', ARRAY['talking_stage', 'needs', 'uncertainty'], ARRAY['confused', 'frustrated'], 2, 50, true),
('reflection', 'It sounds like you''re investing time and energy into something that doesn''t have clear boundaries or commitment, and that can feel both exciting and scary.', ARRAY['talking_stage', 'investment', 'boundaries'], ARRAY['confused', 'worried'], 2, 50, true),
('reflection', 'When you''re in the talking stage, it can be hard to know what you''re allowed to expect or ask for, and that confusion about boundaries is really difficult.', ARRAY['talking_stage', 'boundaries', 'expectations'], ARRAY['confused', 'frustrated'], 2, 50, true),
('reflection', 'It sounds like the talking stage is bringing up questions about your worth and whether you''re enough for someone to want to move forward with, and those doubts can be really painful.', ARRAY['talking_stage', 'self_worth', 'doubt'], ARRAY['hurt', 'worried'], 2, 50, true),

-- TALKING_STAGE - Normalization blocks (7)
('normalization', 'The talking stage is really common in modern dating, and being in one doesn''t mean you''re doing something wrong. Many people find themselves in this undefined space.', ARRAY['talking_stage', 'normal', 'common'], ARRAY['relieved', 'confused'], 1, 50, true),
('normalization', 'It''s normal to feel confused or frustrated in the talking stage, especially if you want more clarity or commitment than the other person seems willing to give. Those feelings are valid.', ARRAY['talking_stage', 'needs', 'frustration'], ARRAY['frustrated', 'confused'], 2, 50, true),
('normalization', 'Many people stay in the talking stage because they''re afraid that asking for clarity will end things, but the uncertainty can be just as painful as a potential rejection. Both are hard, but at least clarity gives you information.', ARRAY['talking_stage', 'fear', 'clarity'], ARRAY['worried', 'reflective'], 2, 50, true),
('normalization', 'It''s common to feel like you''re not allowed to want more from the talking stage, or that asking for commitment means you''re being "too much." But wanting clarity and commitment isn''t too much—it''s a valid need.', ARRAY['talking_stage', 'needs', 'self_worth'], ARRAY['hurt', 'determined'], 2, 50, true),
('normalization', 'Some people stay in the talking stage because they''re getting some of what they need—connection, attention, hope—even if it''s not everything. That can make it hard to leave, even when you know it''s not enough.', ARRAY['talking_stage', 'needs', 'attachment'], ARRAY['confused', 'hurt'], 2, 50, true),
('normalization', 'The talking stage often continues because both people are getting something from the ambiguity—maybe one person gets the benefits without commitment, and the other gets hope without having to face rejection. But that dynamic can be painful for the person who wants more.', ARRAY['talking_stage', 'dynamics', 'needs'], ARRAY['hurt', 'reflective'], 2, 50, true),
('normalization', 'It''s normal to question whether the talking stage will turn into something more, and that uncertainty can make it hard to know how to proceed or what to invest.', ARRAY['talking_stage', 'uncertainty', 'investment'], ARRAY['confused', 'worried'], 2, 50, true),

-- TALKING_STAGE - Exploration blocks (8)
('exploration', 'What do you want from this talking stage? Clarity, commitment, to see where it goes, or something else?', ARRAY['talking_stage', 'needs', 'clarity'], ARRAY['reflective', 'confused'], 1, 50, true),
('exploration', 'What makes it hard to ask for what you want? Fear of rejection, fear of ending things, or something else?', ARRAY['talking_stage', 'fear', 'needs'], ARRAY['worried', 'reflective'], 2, 50, true),
('exploration', 'How is this talking stage meeting your needs, and how is it not?', ARRAY['talking_stage', 'needs', 'awareness'], ARRAY['reflective', 'confused'], 2, 50, true),
('exploration', 'If you could have a conversation about where things stand, what would you want to say?', ARRAY['talking_stage', 'communication', 'needs'], ARRAY['reflective', 'determined'], 2, 50, true),
('exploration', 'What would you need to feel good about continuing in the talking stage, or what would help you decide to move on?', ARRAY['talking_stage', 'needs', 'decision'], ARRAY['reflective', 'confused'], 2, 50, true),
('exploration', 'How has being in the talking stage affected how you see yourself or what you want in relationships?', ARRAY['talking_stage', 'self', 'growth'], ARRAY['reflective', 'hopeful'], 2, 50, true),
('exploration', 'What boundaries do you want to set for yourself in the talking stage?', ARRAY['talking_stage', 'boundaries', 'self'], ARRAY['reflective', 'determined'], 2, 50, true),
('exploration', 'If you could give yourself advice about the talking stage, what would you want to remember?', ARRAY['talking_stage', 'wisdom', 'self'], ARRAY['compassionate', 'reflective'], 2, 50, true),

-- TALKING_STAGE - Reframe blocks (4)
('reframe', 'The talking stage can work for some people who want connection without commitment, but it''s painful when one person wants more than the other is willing to give. If you''re in the talking stage and it''s causing you pain, that''s information. You''re allowed to want clarity and commitment, and you''re allowed to express those needs. If the other person can''t meet them, that doesn''t mean you''re too much—it means you''re not compatible in what you want right now.', ARRAY['talking_stage', 'needs', 'self_worth', 'compatibility'], ARRAY['reflective', 'determined'], 2, 50, true),
('reframe', 'Staying in the talking stage when you want more often comes from a fear of being alone or a fear of rejection, but the uncertainty and lack of clarity can be just as painful as those fears. At least with clarity, you have information to make decisions. Staying in ambiguity because you''re afraid of the answer often means staying in pain because you''re afraid of a different kind of pain.', ARRAY['talking_stage', 'fear', 'clarity', 'pain'], ARRAY['reflective', 'compassionate'], 2, 50, true),
('reframe', 'You deserve to be with someone who wants to be with you in the way you want to be with them. If you want commitment and clarity, you''re allowed to ask for that. If the other person can''t give it, that''s their choice, but it doesn''t mean you should settle for less than what you need. Your needs are valid, and you don''t have to apologize for wanting clarity or commitment.', ARRAY['talking_stage', 'needs', 'self_worth', 'boundaries'], ARRAY['determined', 'reflective'], 2, 50, true),
('reframe', 'Sometimes the talking stage continues because both people are avoiding having a difficult conversation about what they want. But avoiding that conversation doesn''t make the uncertainty go away—it just prolongs it. Having the conversation, even if it leads to an ending, gives you clarity and the ability to move forward, whether that''s together with commitment or apart so you can find someone who wants what you want.', ARRAY['talking_stage', 'communication', 'clarity', 'growth'], ARRAY['hopeful', 'reflective'], 2, 50, true);

